<h4>Pay Grades & Steps</h4>
Federal employees are hired at a general schedule (GS) grade from 1 to 15.
GS grades are based on the combination of a number of variables including education, background, accomplishments, experience, etc.
Inside each grade is a series of 10 steps.
Employees typically start at step 1 of whatever GS grade they are assigned.
(<a href="https://pages.18f.gov/joining-18f/pay-grades/">18F</a>)
We calculated the minimum and maximum salaries of each grade based on the lowest and highest steps available (steps 1 and 10, respectively).

